{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_8","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '560,660p' docs/milestones.md\"","aggregated_output":"- determining whether coupling is instantaneous, filtered, nonlinear, etc.\n\n### Done when\n\n- any edge can be inspected and visualized  \n- the simulator knows where and how input transfers between neurons  \n- coupling rules are configurable and versioned\n\n---\n\n## Milestone 8 — Build the visual input stack\n\nThis milestone is intentionally split because different parts belong to different people.\n\n### Milestone 8A — Canonical stimulus library\n\n**Workload split:** Programming-heavy  \n**Suggested lead:** Jack\n\nBuild generators for:\n\n- flashes  \n- moving bars  \n- drifting gratings  \n- looming stimuli  \n- expansion/contraction flow  \n- rotating flow  \n- translated edge patterns\n\n#### Jack owns\n\n- stimulus generation code  \n- parameterized stimulus configs  \n- playback tooling  \n- serialization for experiment reuse\n\n#### Grant owns\n\n- making sure the stimulus set is scientifically meaningful  \n- defining which stimuli are best for isolating wave effects\n\n#### Done when\n\n- standard stimuli are callable from config  \n- stimuli can be recorded and replayed\n\n---\n\n### Milestone 8B — Retinal / ommatidial sampler\n\n**Workload split:** Shared, leaning math/physics  \n**Suggested lead:** Grant  \n**Implementation support:** Jack\n\n#### Goal\n\nMap world-space visual stimuli into the fly’s retinotopic input representation.\n\n#### Jack owns\n\n- code for image sampling / lattice projection  \n- coordinate system conversions  \n- efficient frame generation  \n- integration with scene playback\n\n#### Grant owns\n\n- defining the retinotopic abstraction  \n- deciding how to approximate the fly’s visual sampling lattice  \n- choosing what resolution and geometry are scientifically defensible  \n- determining how stimuli map into early visual units\n\n#### Done when\n\n- the same scene can be converted into retinal input frames consistently  \n- you can visualize both the world scene and the sampled fly-view representation\n\n---\n\n### Milestone 8C — Scene generator\n\n**Workload split:** Programming-heavy  \n**Suggested lead:** Jack\n\n#### Goal\n\nCreate real visual environments instead of only lab stimuli.\n\n#### Scene system should support\n\n- 2D / 2.5D procedural scenes  \n- moving objects  \n- textured backgrounds  \n- ego-motion  \n- depth layers  \n- scripted events  \n- camera presets\n\n#### Jack owns\n\n- rendering / scene code  \n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' manifests/examples/milestone_1_demo.yaml\"","aggregated_output":"experiment_id: milestone_1_demo_motion_patch\nmilestone: milestone_1\nbrief_version: 1.0.0\nhypothesis_version: 1.0.0\nsubset_name: motion_minimal\ncircuit_name: t4_t5_motion_patch\nmodel_scope: T4/T5 carry morphology-resolved surface dynamics; upstream and downstream partners remain matched reduced or point models.\nstimulus_family: moving_edge\nstimulus_name: simple_moving_edge\nprimary_metric: geometry_sensitive_null_direction_suppression_effect\ncompanion_metrics:\n  - response_latency_to_peak_ms\n  - direction_selectivity_index\n  - geometry_sensitive_shared_output_effect\nsuccess_criteria_ids:\n  - m1_nonzero_shared_output_effect\n  - m1_latency_companion_effect\n  - m1_geometry_dependence\n  - m1_survives_stronger_baseline\n  - m1_seed_parameter_stability\nmust_show_outputs:\n  - stimulus_overview\n  - surface_vs_baseline_split_view\n  - shared_output_trace_overlay\n  - null_direction_suppression_comparison\n  - latency_shift_comparison\n  - topology_ablation_comparison\n  - baseline_challenge_comparison\n  - milestone_decision_panel\nrandom_seed: 11\nseed_sweep:\n  - 11\n  - 17\n  - 23\nnotes: Milestone 1 demo manifest for the same circuit, same simple moving-edge stimulus, matched readout, intact-versus-shuffled topology ablation, and explicit P0/P1 baseline challenge. Numeric pass thresholds remain intentionally unspecified at design-lock time.\ntags:\n  - milestone_1\n  - design_lock\n  - motion_demo\n  - same_circuit_same_stimulus\ncomparison_arms:\n  - arm_id: baseline_p0_intact\n    model_mode: baseline\n    baseline_family: P0\n    topology_condition: intact\n    morphology_condition: intact_synapse_landing_geometry\n    random_seed: 11\n    notes: Canonical point baseline on the matched circuit and shared readout.\n    tags:\n      - canonical_baseline\n      - intact\n  - arm_id: surface_wave_intact\n    model_mode: surface_wave\n    baseline_family: null\n    topology_condition: intact\n    morphology_condition: intact_synapse_landing_geometry\n    random_seed: 11\n    notes: Surface-wave condition with distributed morphology-bound state on T4/T5 only.\n    tags:\n      - surface_wave\n      - intact\n  - arm_id: baseline_p0_shuffled\n    model_mode: baseline\n    baseline_family: P0\n    topology_condition: shuffled\n    morphology_condition: shuffled_synapse_landing_geometry\n    random_seed: 11\n    notes: Canonical point baseline under the same shuffled topology perturbation used for the surface-wave ablation.\n    tags:\n      - canonical_baseline\n      - shuffled\n  - arm_id: surface_wave_shuffled\n    model_mode: surface_wave\n    baseline_family: null\n    topology_condition: shuffled\n    morphology_condition: shuffled_synapse_landing_geometry\n    random_seed: 11\n    notes: Surface-wave condition with synapse landing geometry shuffled to test geometry dependence.\n    tags:\n      - surface_wave\n      - shuffled\n  - arm_id: baseline_p1_intact\n    model_mode: baseline\n    baseline_family: P1\n    topology_condition: intact\n    morphology_condition: intact_synapse_landing_geometry\n    random_seed: 11\n    notes: Stronger reduced baseline with explicit integration current or delay structure under intact topology.\n    tags:\n      - stronger_baseline\n      - intact\n  - arm_id: baseline_p1_shuffled\n    model_mode: baseline\n    baseline_family: P1\n    topology_condition: shuffled\n    morphology_condition: shuffled_synapse_landing_geometry\n    random_seed: 11\n    notes: Stronger reduced baseline under shuffled topology for the same comparison family.\n    tags:\n      - stronger_baseline\n      - shuffled\noutput_bundle:\n  metrics_json: outputs/milestone_1/milestone_1_demo_motion_patch/metrics/summary_metrics.json\n  summary_table_csv: outputs/milestone_1/milestone_1_demo_motion_patch/metrics/per_condition_summary.csv\n  plots:\n    - id: shared_output_trace_overlay\n      path: outputs/milestone_1/milestone_1_demo_motion_patch/plots/shared_output_trace_overlay.png\n    - id: null_direction_suppression_comparison\n      path: outputs/milestone_1/milestone_1_demo_motion_patch/plots/null_direction_suppression_comparison.png\n    - id: latency_shift_comparison\n      path: outputs/milestone_1/milestone_1_demo_motion_patch/plots/latency_shift_comparison.png\n    - id: topology_ablation_comparison\n      path: outputs/milestone_1/milestone_1_demo_motion_patch/plots/topology_ablation_comparison.png\n    - id: baseline_challenge_comparison\n      path: outputs/milestone_1/milestone_1_demo_motion_patch/plots/baseline_challenge_comparison.png\n  ui_states:\n    - id: stimulus_overview\n      path: outputs/milestone_1/milestone_1_demo_motion_patch/ui/stimulus_overview.json\n    - id: surface_vs_baseline_split_view\n      path: outputs/milestone_1/milestone_1_demo_motion_patch/ui/surface_vs_baseline_split_view.json\n    - id: milestone_decision_panel\n      path: outputs/milestone_1/milestone_1_demo_motion_patch/ui/milestone_decision_panel.json\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
