{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_63","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/pipeline_notes.md | sed -n '150,250p'\"","aggregated_output":"   150\t- subset extraction keeps only rows where both endpoints are in the requested\n   151\t  root set so grouping the synapse registry by `(pre_root_id, post_root_id,\n   152\t  neuropil, nt_type)` reproduces the same-scope edge-level `syn_count`\n   153\t\n   154\t`config.paths.manifest_json` now also records:\n   155\t\n   156\t- `_coupling_contract_version` and `_coupling_contract` at the manifest header\n   157\t- a per-root `coupling_bundle` block that points to the local synapse registry,\n   158\t  root-local anchor maps, the root-local coupling index, and any explicit\n   159\t  edge-bundle references already built for that root\n   160\t- the design-note path and design-note version each bundle conforms to\n   161\t\n   162\tThe default Milestone 7 semantics are intentionally fixed early:\n   163\t\n   164\t- topology family: `distributed_patch_cloud`\n   165\t- fallback hierarchy: `surface_patch_cloud` ->\n   166\t  `skeleton_segment_cloud` -> `point_neuron_lumped`\n   167\t- kernel family: `separable_rank_one_cloud`\n   168\t- sign representation: `categorical_sign_with_signed_weight`\n   169\t- delay representation: `nonnegative_delay_ms_per_synapse_or_delay_bin`\n   170\t- delay model: `constant_zero_ms`\n   171\t- multi-synapse aggregation: `sum_over_synapses_preserving_sign_and_delay_bins`\n   172\t- source/target cloud normalization: `sum_to_one_per_component`\n   173\t\n   174\t`docs/coupling_bundle_design.md` is the authoritative Milestone 7 decision note;\n   175\tlater tickets should cite it instead of re-litigating the default coupling\n   176\tfamily, fallback hierarchy, or sign/delay/aggregation invariants.\n   177\t\n   178\t### Stimulus bundle contract\n   179\t\n   180\tMilestone 8A now reserves one explicit visual-stimulus discovery surface under\n   181\tthe versioned contract `stimulus_bundle.v1`.\n   182\t\n   183\tThe library-owned default layout is:\n   184\t\n   185\t- `data/processed/stimuli/bundles/<stimulus_family>/<stimulus_name>/<parameter_hash>/stimulus_bundle.json`:\n   186\t  authoritative stimulus descriptor and replay metadata\n   187\t- `data/processed/stimuli/bundles/<stimulus_family>/<stimulus_name>/<parameter_hash>/stimulus_frames.npz`:\n   188\t  optional cached frame stack derived from the descriptor\n   189\t- `data/processed/stimuli/bundles/<stimulus_family>/<stimulus_name>/<parameter_hash>/stimulus_preview.gif`:\n   190\t  optional human-review preview animation\n   191\t- `data/processed/stimuli/aliases/<alias_family>/<alias_name>/<parameter_hash>.json`:\n   192\t  compatibility alias record pointing old names at the canonical bundle\n   193\t\n   194\tContract notes:\n   195\t\n   196\t- bundle paths, metadata serialization, alias paths, and discovery now live in\n   197\t  `flywire_wave.stimulus_contract` rather than ad hoc script code\n   198\t- the descriptor metadata records the stimulus-contract version, design-note\n   199\t  version, canonical stimulus family/name, deterministic seed, RNG family,\n   200\t  parameter snapshot, parameter hash, spatial frame, temporal sampling, and\n   201\t  luminance convention\n   202\t- the default representation family is `hybrid_descriptor_plus_cache`:\n   203\t  descriptor metadata is authoritative and frame caches are optional\n   204\t- timing is always expressed in milliseconds with `sample_hold` frame playback\n   205\t- the canonical spatial frame is `visual_field_degrees_centered` with origin at\n   206\t  the aperture center, positive azimuth to the right, positive elevation up,\n   207\t  and pixel centers as sampling points\n   208\t- luminance is always interpreted as linear values in `[0.0, 1.0]` with neutral\n   209\t  gray `0.5`; signed contrast parameters are deltas relative to that neutral\n   210\t  gray\n   211\t- compatibility aliases may rename stimulus family/name, but they may not\n   212\t  mutate seed, timing, spatial frame, luminance semantics, or generator\n   213\t  parameters\n   214\t\n   215\tThe practical replay key is the tuple `(contract_version, stimulus_family,\n   216\tstimulus_name, parameter_hash)`. Later manifests and tooling should resolve\n   217\tstimuli through the library contract instead of hardcoded frame filenames.\n   218\t\n   219\t`docs/stimulus_bundle_design.md` is the authoritative Milestone 8A decision\n   220\tnote; later tickets should cite it instead of re-litigating the representation\n   221\tfamily, replay semantics, or coordinate/luminance conventions.\n   222\t\n   223\t### Offline coupling inspection contract\n   224\t\n   225\tMilestone 7 now also defines one deterministic offline inspection workflow for\n   226\tedge-level coupling review:\n   227\t\n   228\t- `scripts/08_coupling_inspection.py` reads the local synapse registry, one or\n   229\t  more edge bundles, the matching root-local anchor maps, and whichever local\n   230\t  geometry artifacts are needed by the realized anchor types\n   231\t- output goes to `config.paths.coupling_inspection_dir/edges-<sorted-edge-slug>/`\n   232\t- the report is static: `index.html`, `report.md`, `summary.json`, `edges.txt`,\n   233\t  per-edge detail JSON, and SVG panels for presynaptic readout plus\n   234\t  postsynaptic landing geometry\n   235\t- each edge emits compact `pass`, `warn`, `fail`, or `blocked` QA flags for\n   236\t  mapping coverage, anchor-map consistency, component integrity, cloud\n   237\t  normalization, and delay sanity\n   238\t- the detail JSON keeps the metric table, blocked-synapse rows, and aggregate\n   239\t  component rows in a review-friendly format so regressions can be asserted in\n   240\t  fixture tests\n   241\t- `scripts/09_milestone7_readiness.py` layers a fixture-suite check plus a\n   242\t  registry/subset/coupling-contract audit on top of the coupling inspection\n   243\t  bundle and writes `milestone_7_readiness.md` plus\n   244\t  `milestone_7_readiness.json` into the same deterministic report directory\n   245\t- `make milestone7-readiness` is the one-command entrypoint for the shipped\n   246\t  offline Milestone 7 verification pass; it uses\n   247\t  `config/milestone_7_verification.yaml` plus a tracked edge list so the local\n   248\t  audit can run entirely from cached mesh and skeleton assets plus the curated\n   249\t  Milestone 7 verification synapse snapshot\n   250\t\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
